Title: Describe Functionality of User Interface
Description: Please view and describe the the functionality of the screenshot of a mobile application
Keywords: image, tag, picture, tagging, screenshot, mobile, application, user, interface, functionality
Answer.HighLevel: This is the screen that allows a person to sign into the program by using their site login credentials for their account, signing in using their facebook account, or signing in using their Google account.
Answer.LowLevel1: The top of the Get Full Profile sign in allows you to enter your name and directly below your email to access the sites information.
Answer.LowLevel2: In the center of the page is an option to click next once you have entered your login credentials.
Answer.LowLevel3: The facebook alternative login information is located in the center of page towards bottom. It has the Facebook logo button to click to access the site.
Answer.LowLevel4: The last option at the bottom of the login page uses the Google button logo to gain access to the site.

Title: Describe Functionality of User Interface
Description: Please view and describe the the functionality of the screenshot of a mobile application
Keywords: image, tag, picture, tagging, screenshot, mobile, application, user, interface, functionality
Answer.HighLevel: This screen shows a forgot password form, allowing the user to retrieve their password.
Answer.LowLevel1: There is a back button up in the top-left, and clicking it goes back to the previous screen.
Answer.LowLevel2: The top portion of the form contains a text box for the user to enter either their email or mobile number.
Answer.LowLevel3: Below the email/mobile phone text box is a “send” button. When clicked, this submits the form and the user will receive an email/text message containing further instructions.
Answer.LowLevel4: The top right has an “X”, which allows the user to close the form. This functions just like the “back” button.
